              <div class="quotetitle">devoid wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Techie_Jim wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Bought the US T28 tank destroyer yesterday and it seemed like one of the only vehicles to ever 'live up to the hype' with respect to armour.  (Though I will say that several patches ago the King Tiger did as well.)  I faced directly at opponents and shot them with great effect.  They shot back at me and I took a bunch of bounces and no damage, even from what I knew to be large calibre weapons.  It was a good time.  I've yet to unlock the largest gun either but this is looking to be a fun tank to play against silly pubbies that want to stand off and shoot - well, they're welcome to do that!</div><br /><br />and much like the ferdi, when you start moving towards them slowly, shrugging off their attacks and continuing to punch holes in them, they get very very uncomfortable. as though by relocating anywhere in a TD is a violation of the conventions of pubbie tank war.<br /><br />roll three T28s together, all moving the same direction, it is very scary.</div><br /><br />That's weird.<br /><br />My T28 is full of holes from the front.  The only time I had scratches is when I managed to angle the hull and fired at them with a rock covering the flat cheek.  Many tier 8s can punch it from the front and the sides and rear are paper thin.<br /><br />The best time I had last night is when BJ, fresh and I derped our way through Himmelsdorf as 3 derp KV-2s and top tanks.

              

              
              
            </div>
