          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle">Techie_Jim wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Bought the US T28 tank destroyer yesterday and it seemed like one of the only vehicles to ever 'live up to the hype' with respect to armour.  (Though I will say that several patches ago the King Tiger did as well.)  I faced directly at opponents and shot them with great effect.  They shot back at me and I took a bunch of bounces and no damage, even from what I knew to be large calibre weapons.  It was a good time.  I've yet to unlock the largest gun either but this is looking to be a fun tank to play against silly pubbies that want to stand off and shoot - well, they're welcome to do that!</div><br /><br />The T28 with the big gun is fun. One bit of advice is save all your free XP, you need 22K I think, for when you go to the T95 or you'll be a very sad panda. You have to upgrade the tracks to upgrade from the stock gun which is equivalent to mid-tier T28 gun(if my memory is correct). The upgraded tracks let you use the big gun from T28 to start with.  It's absolutely a blast to roll in a T28/95 with an Ars platoon with the heavies shooting over you as you barrel down on the other side. Works really well with American tanks with their serious turret armor but weaker hull armor.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
