              Introductions: Forum newbie (long time reader on Ars, only recently stumbled into the forums and started reading)<br /><br />Awesome, introductions done.<br /><br />I just started playing this game this weekend and it hooked me by surprise. Had hit one of those lulls where I was looking for something new to play so I was going down the list of F2P games that people talk way too much about. Wasn't expecting much, still had a bit of a stigma in my mind attached to F2P games. This one was actually the last one on the list and I hated it for the first 45 minutes, but then hey, 2 hours later, still playing!<br /><br />Well, the entire weekend later I'm still at it.<br /><br />So the content: As a freshman tanker, what nationality do you think is a good one to dive into first? Not just in terms of learning curve but in terms of long term investment? I don't want to get a few weeks down a nation's tech tree to find out that their later tier tanks suck and I have to start over. (I also realize that a lot will probably come down to personal taste, but hearing from people who've gotten a little further into their trees is always nice).<br /><br />I've already begun working on Germany and am actually between tier III and IV across the entire tree (that's right, I've got pretty much one of each tank at my current tech level).<br /><br />Thoughts? And any objections to a completely random person on the internet hopping into the Ars WoT channel (I could've sworn I read something about one earlier in the thread)? Keep in mind, I don't want to just stay a random person from the internet, but hey, you gotta start somewhere.

              

              
              
