          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Coming from a fairly new player as well (only up to tier 6), if I had it to do over again I would probably go American.<br /><br />They get heavy tanks 2 tiers earlier than the Germans, if that's your thing. Though same for the Russians. In general the Russian tanks take hits better, but are painfully slow. In my experience (up to KV-1), the Russian tanks are really hard to do a lot of damage with though. My T1 HT (American) can't take as many hits but I can usually wreck a few guys before I go down. Further down the line, the T29 is a tank people rave about.<br /><br />On the other hand, if you <span style="font-weight: bold">don't</span> want a heavy tank the German line has some pretty nice tank destroyers. I'm hesitating to buy the tier 6 because it really doesn't seem an upgrade from the tier 5 once you take the higher matchmaking into account. Once you get to tier 8, they're amazing.<br /><br />This is really just a new player's gut instinct, so take it with a grain of salt, but I haven't really been a big fan of the German line that I went with. I consistently get wrecked by a myriad of American tanks and keep kicking myself for not going with them earlier.<br /><br />P.S. Screw artillery and everyone who plays them!  <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/razz.png" alt=":p" title="Razz" /><br /><br />P.P.S. Avoid any light tanks like the plague. They get matched on average about 3 tiers higher than them, since they're considered scouts. What that means is you won't touch anyone, and will die on one hit. Not fun. Not much XP either.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
