        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Hello Defiant107,<br />There are several sweet rides in each nationality.  Some tanks are better suited to different play styles, and are very VERY short lived and frustrating if you play certain tanks &quot;wrong&quot;.  The game is developed, owned and maintained by Russians.  There is a &quot;bit&quot; of bias towards the Russian line, and thus far, certain Russian tanks (non premium) that seem to make a profit just by showing up.  KV's line seems to be one, though it recently underwent major surgery, so I have kept only a couple.<br /><br />It appears that all lines have a plateau, it is pretty easy to get to about tier 4 or 5, but (depending on the line) it tends to be a slow grind to get to the  next tier, where it is a bit less of a grind.  At 7 and above it just takes a long time to progress through.<br /><br />I found the German line of arty fun through the Hummel, where it is a long reach to get to the GwPanther, which is highly thought of by my regular plt mates.  <br />In the French line, the AMX 40 is usually not spoken of in polite company as the resulting denigrating comments are not fit for young ears.  Get past that and you unlock the ELC AMX which sorta a clown car of death.  Great humor, speed and acceleration like Hammie the Squirrel big gun, sloooowwww reload, soft and squishy.  Arguably the most entertaining and frustrating tank at Tier 5 in the game. <br /><br />American TDs have two branches, the turreted line including the M18 are fun for me.  Not good brawlers by any stretch, but good TDs.  The American line has some very good tanks in the line, the Tier V M5 Sherman is very formidable with the baby derp (I have started calling it the BURP) and has quick reload for a BURP.  It is not for going toe to toe with a VK3601H, more like peek and smash and duck fast, like a pie in the face.  The Tier 6 M4AE2 and M4AE8 follow, the E2 is slower and has fairly good armor, I don't have that one, the E8 or &quot;easy 8&quot; has great mobility and maneuverability and quick firing decent penetrating gun.  One notable feature of the American line is that they tend to have the best gun depression.  This is particularly noticeable when on very hilly maps.  This in turn means that there are &quot;great&quot; spots to roll up to in an American tanks that are foolish to go to with most other lines.<br /><br />So, unless there is a particular reason to focus solely on one nationality, you may wish to consider multiple lines concurrently.  Pursuing multiple lines adds variety to your stable, and makes it a little easier to Plt up with other Arsians.<br /><br />Platooning up with 1 or 2 other Arsians and using Team Speak (or other suitable voice comms) will do wonders for your learning curve, and your level of enjoyment as well.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
