        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Best advice when starting out is to pick a nation (not France, as mentioned) and go up more than one line (ideally, two, or your pace upward will be pretty slow) <span style="font-style: italic">in the same nation</span>. Because modules on various vehicles, such as guns, radios, engines (but never tracks) are shared across different lines, your progress up multiple lines in one nation will benefit from cross-unlocking and, thus, be faster!<br /><br />I would recommend the US as the best choice for a first nation, since it features the most well-balanced tanks and great TDs. But you won't go wrong starting with Soviets, Germans or Americans. If you are sure you want to pursue artillery, though, I would recommend Germany.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
