              As a relative newbie (a few weeks prior to Unison), there's some great advice.  I second the US line.  My friend Kaeos has ground the TD line and enjoys them quite a bit.  He's also gone up to the KV-3 in the Russian line, but after seeing some of the US line, I think he's decided to go US heavy as well. I have ground all four lines to some degree...and two of the most painful grinds in the game (imho), the French light line and to the German Pz IV.  Don't do the french line first.  I ended up free xp'ing through parts of the AMX 38 and 40...just awful.  I did it to make sure I could get an ELC, which I thoroughly enjoy, but more on that later.  The AMX 1375 was a blast to play pre-patch, but I haven't played it much since the patch because I've really enjoyed the US line.<br /><br />The Pz IV is a great tank (along with some of the tanks after), but the grind (although not as bad as the french lights) is still bad because of the 38na. It's not a bad tank, just gets screwed in Matchmaking (MM)all...the...time.<br /><br />If I had to do it all again, I'd explore the US heavy/td line first...then maybe the Germans and French.<br /><br />As far as the ELC...well I have to brag a little bit.  Granted, it was x2 and I have premium (for 1 more week, I think), but still...<br /><br />Victory!<br />Battle: Malinovka Wednesday, August 08, 2012 10:27:14 AM<br />Vehicle: ELC AMX<br />Experience received: 2,912 (x2 for the first victory each day)<br />Credits received: 44,275 (compensation for damage caused by allies: 395)<br />Battle Achievements: Mastery Badge: &quot;1st Class&quot;<br /><br />It was a standard map, for once.  My team was just sitting there camping, so I went across the field to spot for a little bit.  Survived...then went up the hill and back down around the school house and spotted some more.  Did the hill again and went down past the school for arty.  We ended up winning thanks to great arty.

              

              
              
