              So I was finally able to play some more last night and actually managed to destroy a T1 for my first (and so far only) kill! That was my only kill out of about 6 battles I did. I also bought the T2 medium tank which seems to hit harder than the T1 I started with but I get paired up with much higher tier tanks when I play with the T2. Right now I'm just trying to grind out the stuff I need to buy a tier 3 tank and move on with the tutorial.<br /><br />I think right now my biggest issue is just paying attention and making sure no one is sneaking up behind me. I tend to try and stay with a group of tanks but the random battles rarely have anyone using the light tanks for actual scouting so many times an enemy tank will come out of nowhere and by the time the first shot hits I'm too far from cover to do anything.<br /><br />I got into a whack-a-mole type combat with a few tanks where I would pop out take a shot then roll back behind a rock and they would do the same until one of us was destroyed. Still having fun just wish I had more time to play.

              

              
              
