          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle">defiant107 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Sounds good, after poking around the equipment I got the impression it was all one-time use. But while on the subject, what's the going opinion on equipment and consumables (both at my low-tier and later on)? Is it worth it to keep your tank stocked with maybe a repair kit? Is the ventalation worth it? And anything else along those lines?</div><br />Equipment stays on your tank indefinitely.  Some equipment can be removed for free; most equipment cannot be removed unless you pay in game gold - which is arguably one of the best uses of gold.  Consumables come in 2 types: first is consumed on use (like a repair kit) and must be replaced, second is consumed as soon as you enter a battle (like 100 octane gas).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">defiant107 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I've come across a situation or two where maybe having a consumable to repair a track and keep moving might've kept me alive a tiny bit longer, but most of the time I pretty much die and nothing would've saved me, save for being smarter.</div><br />I didn't really use consumables on my vehicles till I got into the mid-tiers and made credits more consistantly.  When you first start are you are credit-starved for advancement.  Later you typically have credits (if not to burn then at least to easily cover your 'operating' costs) and are experience-starved.  My suggestion is to wait until you're at about tier5 and have a couple good credit-earners before you worry about consumables.<br />Without malice - you're probably not experienced enough yet for them to make much of a difference in your success.  <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/smile.png" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">defiant107 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">And as far as stuff like ventilation (at least I think that's what it's called), I'm switching tanks often enough right now that I don't think it's really worth it, but does it ever become worth it? If so, what tier would you say?</div><br />Not until you start making significantly more credits than you need.  I know there are differences but most gear - like vents or rammers - are in the neighbourhood of 500k credits apiece and can only be dismounted for gold.  Make sure you a) like the tank and b) have credits to burn without impeding your progress.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">defiant107 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Final note, when you blow up, do you lose all your ammunition and consumables?</div>Nope.

              

              
              
            </div>
