        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Regarding consumables.<br />Repair, fire extinguisher, and first aid are only used on command.<br />High octane fuel is used each match, so is ridiculously expensive at low tiers.<br />Consumables are NOT destroyed unless used.<br />As these consumables typically cost 3000 credits or more, using them can eat up your profit margin and then some while running low tier.  Not using them and (maybe) losing the match verses using them and (maybe) winning the match can be a tough ROI calculation.  <br /><br />Regarding Equipment.<br />Equipment is not normally destroyed.  I do not think it impacts repair costs either, but I never bothered to test that theory.<br />Equipment can be moved from tank to tank, though except for binocs, camo net, and tool box, you have to pay 10 gold to dismount (complex equipment).  Not all equipment is compatible with all tanks.  Some tanks get tracked a lot.  If that tank has the option for a suspension upgrade, like 5ton torsion bars, adding that complex equipment will also enhance the durability of the tracks/suspension in terms of being able to take more damage before becoming &quot;tracked&quot;.<br /><br />For low tiers, as in 4 and below, it is pretty tough to justify much beyond a camo net, maybe a set of binos for a TD or Scout.  After Tier5 or 6, or as soon as you get into cannons that take 12 seconds or more to load, a gun rammer becomes a highly prized add on.  There are equipment sales periodically, where the equipment is at 1/2 price, that is the time to splurge on rammers, vents, etc.<br /><br />If you happen to be flush with cash, Vents, Rammer, Gun laying drive or Vertical Stabilizer are a pretty standard load out.  TDs may take Optics or Binocs.  Arty and TDs usually leave a spot for camo net regardless of what else they might want. Heavies almost always go for Rammer plus GLD or VS, third spot is usually the only one not heartily agreed on (from my observations) as the other two have an impact on how fast you can engage a target and cause damage.  Do Damage, get Credits.  No Damage, few credits (except for passive scouting).<br /><br />Once you have progressed past Tier 6 or 7, you may find that you just love driving certain lower tier tanks, that is the time to Pimp Your Ride with GLD, Rammer, and Vents ( or whatever is preferred for that tank and your preferences).

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
