          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle">Sog wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So IS-4s and IS-7s are about useless for competitive play now?</div><br /><br />For our maps, yes. We do use the occasional IS-4, but a Maus has more HP so if we have a good Maus driver we'll often take that. That said, we do have one guy who is just about done with his 4th skill on his IS-4, so any time we need an IS-4 he gets first nod. <br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">corts wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'd be interested in how the E50Ms are being utilized.</div><br /><br />They are fast, have a good gun, and can ram other mediums hard enough that it might as well be a second shot. Good view range too, and it occasionally bounces things, although the size is a bit of an issue. They are working well so far for us. <br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">socoj2 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Kestrel how do i get into some Clan wars action?</div><br /><br />Well, I play with the goons, so that has a requirement of :tenbux:, along with posting there for a while, etc. If you have a T10 tank and non-terrible stats however, there are numerous land holding clans that will take you. Some are really bad, some are decent. If you go down that route, only look at clans that are holding land in Europe, because they at least are competent enough to make a bit of gold. <br /><br />Really though, I'd recommend trying to organize ARS landing battles, and just getting used to CW. There should be enough ars players around to at least do landing battles a couple of times a week. You could also try talking to various clans to see if you can become their allies, and hold a landing zone for them. With the patch a while back that prevented land holding clans from applying to landing battles, landing zones are a huge risk. Having an ally hold that lets you relocate your chip stacks elsewhere, and so hold more land, push on more fronts, etc.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
     
</div>

